-- Japan Equity Movers: Fuji Electric, Nomura, Pronexus, Tokyo Dome
-- B y   Y o s h i a k i   N o h a r a
-- 2012-03-23T01:04:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/japan-equity-movers-fuji-electric-nomura-pronexus-tokyo-dome.html
Nikkei 225  falls 1%. Topix drops
0.9%, led by brokerages. Volume 29% below 10-day avg. in first
39 mins. of trading.  Gainers:
*Fuji Electric +2.3%; wins biomass equipment order in U.S.,
Nikkei reports
*Pronexus +5.8%; raises dividend forecast to 9 yen from 8 yen
*Toko +19%; to sell CB, shares to Murata Manufacturing to raise
as much as 3.4b yen
*Tokyo Electric Power +2.8%; utility to seek up to 900b yen,
Asahi reports minutes before market close yesterday
*Tokyo Dome gains 1.9%; PT raised to 330 yen from 240 yen at
Mitsubishi UFJ Morgan Stanley  Decliners:
*Dai-ichi Life Insurance -3.3%; heads for 5.9% drop on week,
first weekly loss in 8 weeks
*Nomura Holdings -2.6%; starts internal investigation of whether
it was source of confidential information used for alleged
 insider trading  by Chuo Mitsui Asset Trust, Nikkei reports  To contact the reporter on this story:
